isoiec80000:term-t10-86.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "kerma"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t10-86.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "K"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t10-86.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "10-86.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t10-86.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t10-86.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """for uncharged ionizing radiation, differential quotient of stem:[E_\"tr\"] with respect to stem:[m], where stem:[E_\"tr\"] is the mean sum of the initial kinetic energies (<<iso80000-4>>) of all the charged ionizing particles liberated in a mass (<<iso80000-4>>) stem:[m] of a material:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
K = (\"d\"E_(\"tr\"))/(\"d\"m)
++++
"""@en ;
  skos:note """[stem%unnumbered]
++++
1 \"unitsml(Gy)\" = 1 \"unitsml(J/kg)\"
++++

See the remarks for <<t10-81.1>>.

The name \"kerma\" is derived from Kinetic Energy Released in MAtter (or MAss or MAterial).

The quantity stem:[\"d\"E_\"tr\"] includes also the kinetic energy of the charged particles emitted in the decay of excited atoms, molecules, or nuclei.

When the mass element stem:[\"d\"m] consists of air the term air kerma is used. It can be convenient to refer to a value of air kerma in free space or at a point inside a material different from air, e.g. to the air kerma at a point inside a water phantom.

In report 85a of the ICRU a definition with an equivalent meaning is given as:

The kerma, stem:[K], for ionizing uncharged particles, is the quotient of stem:[\"d\"E_\"tr\"] by stem:[\"d\"m], where stem:[\"d\"E_\"tr\"] is the mean sum of the initial kinetic energies of all the charged particles liberated in a mass stem:[\"d\"m] of a material by the uncharged particles incident on stem:[\"d\"m]:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
K = (\"d\"E_\"tr\")/(\"d\"m).
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-Gy ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/kg ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^2*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-10 .